		<hr size="1">Well damn...I was about to give you "what for" from asking where the Paladin Site is, after you said you spent all that time on Caster's Realm.  However, with a brief search, it seems that Baelish has hidden the link to PoN (Paladins of Norrath).  With some work, you can find it...but it's no longer easily clicked.</P><P>Anyway, it's <A HREF="http://eq.crgaming.com/pon" TARGET="_BLANK">http://eq.crgaming.com/pon</A> (link looks familiar, huh? <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle>).</P><P>As for LDoN armor and crap - can't tell you.  It will be months, and months before I can purchase anything worthwhile from an Adventure Merchant.  So, I play any dungeon I want w/o a care towards what camp site has what to "buy".</P><P>Don't really worry about your STR.  It will come.  Almost every piece of Paladin gear has STR on it somewhere.  Worry about STA - it's freakishly hard to raise.  That's the problem I'm running into right now.  Can't find any decent armor for my level that has good STA.</P><P>However, I spent way too much time concentrating on WIS.  You don't find too many Paladins with an <B>unbuffed</b> (ie no KEI) WIS of approx 190. (depends what weapons I'm holding)</P><P>That's too much...it's a waste of a stat.  So I'm dropping WIS items for STA.  But I would recommend getting your WIS over 100.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
