		<hr size="1">Hello Willoww.  I am level 65 and not an uber-Pally by any stretch.</P><P>The best camp for a Paladin is Takish because our best armour can be earned there.  This of course implies you are willing to think long term and max out the theme to get it.</P><P>Other than stuns we have group heals.  In an overpull situation just do a group heal to pull the angry wee beasties off the finger waggling classes and onto you.  This might just buy enough time for your crowd control person to get things sorted out.</P><P>Paladins miss too often for weapon damage to make any difference to aggro.  The ideal weapons for aggro are ones that proc some kind of Stun, although I would hazard against those with a knockback effect.  It makes sense (if you can manage it) to carry two main weapons: a high aggro weapon for when you are MA, and a low aggro weapon for when you are in a support role.  For both weapons try to get the delay as low as possible, and the damage as high as you can.  </P><P>Most paladins prefer to fight with a 2H weapon.  I mostly use a <a "href=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=17345">Resplendent War Maul</a> which drops of Vallon Zek, a level 70 MoB in Drunder.  Apart from generally doing more damage than 1H, it is also good practice for weilding your epic when the time comes.</P><P>Different things are important at different times of the game.  In the early days AC is vital.  Depending on what gear you have an what race you play you might find yourself working on STR or WIS a little bit.  As a High Elf I had to spend a bit of effort on STR, but a Dwarf might be thinking more about WIS.  From about level 40 your resists are important because you'll be starting to raid.  I am at a point in the game where I wish I had more mana for those all important group heals so I've been working hard on improving this in the last couple of months.  To put this in perspective I am one Tallon Zek kill away from entering the Elemental Planes.</P><P>HP is always important at any level.  I carry about 7.5 khp when I'm raid buffed (with all important stats sitting on 305), and about 4.3 khp unbuffed.  Others in my guild who are the same level have around 1000 HP more (although I have not yet worked on HP AAXP - such a slacker).  The uber-Pallies are up around 10.5 khp.</P><P>Your question about LoH tells me you have some very nice gear for a Paladin at your level.  LoH does improve with your progression in the game.  It was designed for those of us who remember the joy of getting that first piece of leather armour.  Back then nobody had heard of twinking and LoH would be just like a complete heal, at least until level 40-ish as I recall.  Then came the AAXP to convert LoH to a complete heal.</P><P>I like to keep all weapons skills maxxed because you never know what useful PAL only item might drop off the next MoB.  Even 1H can be valuable if it procs some nice buff.</P><P>I hope this helps.</P><P><BR><a HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=558247&resize=true"> <img src="http://www.poutinet.com/sigs/KohiSig.jpg" border=0> </a></P><P>Message edited by: Kohinoor (1/14/2004 10:53:05 AM)<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
